  "reference_number": "BEL0023",
  "remarks": "\nMikhail Damarnacki is Commander of the Special Purpose Police Unit of Gomel (OMON). In his role as Commander, Damarnacki bears responsibility for the actions of OMON officers in Gomel. Damarnacki therefore bears responsibility for the serious human rights violations carried out by OMON officers following the election of 9 August, in particular arbitrary arrests and ill‐treatment, including torture, of people believed to be peaceful demonstrators",
